            "body": "@coderforlife thanks for following up, I'm happy to have learn there was a change of heart to some degree.\r\n\r\nIt looks like that's not quite a substitute though, it's more of an implementation of the entire function block inside the docstring (not at all a bad thing) and it looks like it targets pure c rather than something for instance using Eigen./includes and additional linker flags.\r\n\r\nSo I don't think #556 should be closed, but thank you for chiming in and hopefully bringing attention back to it.",
